definition: to check/to examine/to inspect/to exercise restraint
variant of 視|视[shi4]/variant of 示[shi4]

sentences.english: Let's view justice in the large sense.
sentences.chinese: 让我们以大格局来检视正义。

sentences.english: If the user is not permitted to see any child nodes, an empty collection is returned.
sentences.chinese: 如果使用者不允许检视任何子节点，则会传回空集合。

sentences.english: Unique see-through-window & lighting device for easy monitoring.
sentences.chinese: 独到的视明窗及照明设备，检视功能，事半功倍。

sentences.english: On the class diagram, select the type for which you want to view the base class or interface.
sentences.chinese: 在类别图表上，选取要检视其基底类别或介面的型别。

sentences.english: Can view the first round of brake oil pipe is, the adequacy of tire pressure.
sentences.chinese: 可先检视该轮制动管路是否漏油，轮胎气压是否充足。

sentences.english: The stewards will inspect the course to see if racing is possible.
sentences.chinese: 那些干事将检视赛马场看是否适宜比赛。

sentences.english: For a single-file Web page, switch to Source view.
sentences.chinese: 若是单一档案网页，请切换至原始码检视。

sentences.english: Instead he will review how you treated other people, particularly those in need.
sentences.chinese: 他会检视你如何对人，特别是那些有需要的人。

sentences.english: Chapter Two examines the foreign face of Dublin caused by British domination.
sentences.chinese: 第二章检视因英国统治造成都柏林的陌生市景。

sentences.english: It is scrolled fully into view within its parent container, if any.
sentences.chinese: 如果有父容器的话，则该点可完全卷动至检视内。

sentences.english: Some 200 inspectors were dispatched across the nation for closer inspections.
sentences.chinese: 约200名稽查员被派遣至台湾各地做更仔细的检视。

sentences.english: Process Lasso lets you do this right inside its built-in process viewer.
sentences.chinese: 拉索进程，让你这个权利，在其内建的检视过程。

sentences.english: Here you can configure the appearance of the thumbnail view of your scan picture gallery.
sentences.chinese: 在此您可以设定您的扫瞄图像集的缩图检视。

sentences.english: PleASe send AS additional detailed information and also a few metro of sample of these two kinds for our examination.
sentences.chinese: 请寄来更详细的资料和几米此两种货的样品以便检视。

sentences.english: But perhaps scrutinizing all those vacua is unnecessary;
sentences.chinese: 但或许我们并不需要检视所有的真空。

sentences.english: I am traveling on in time in my review of these arguments.
sentences.chinese: 我正在依时间顺序逐个检视那些论点。

definition: to observe and form a judgment
to consider/to give serious consideration to sth/consideration
to comb through (historical documents etc)/to unravel
to examine/to cast a critical eye over (especially in the context of introspection)
to collect and organize (papers etc)/to archive (data)/to summarize (evidence etc)/summary
variant of 聯結|联结[lian2 jie2]
to screen/to discriminate/to reexamine a case/screening (of applicants etc)
